	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=2269><span id= >Oakshot</span></a><br><span id=notbold>1 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.16]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>You think this is BAD?<br><br>You can do some incredible tricks with the weighed axe, if you're a good enough player.&nbsp;&nbsp;Anyone who thinks a warrior is just about toggling on attack and sitting back had better not be in my group.<br><br>With appropriate timing, and in the correct circumstances, this thing would be incredible!  On one of our Hate raids, one of the secondary tanks using a weighted axe was able to damage-taunt (not using taunt button) the Maestro off of the primary tank who was dual weilding AND higher level!  (Hence his damage modifiers, etc, were higher.)<br><br>As for the negative stats, any decent tank this high level is nearly topped out anyway.  Standard buffs would cover these negatives with no problem at all.<br><br>I shudder to think what a crit would look like with one of these. I think my friend's record for a crit with the Weighted Axe is in the realm of 385 without disciplines.</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
